title: Fallen
description: Via interviews with grieving families, this heart-wrenching documentary pays tribute to police officers who were killed in the line of duty.

title: Farewell Ferris Wheel
description: From the perspective of both owners and migrant workers, this visually rich documentary offers a nuanced look into the U.S. carnival industry.

title: Fearless
description: On a journey from Brazil to the Las Vegas championships, professional bull riders risk it all to earn money, respect and titles.
actors: Adriano Moraes, J.B. Mauney, Silvano Alves, Kaique Pacheco

title: Feel Rich
description: Talking squarely to the hip-hop generation, musicians, athletes and others outline the benefits of exercise, a healthy diet and spiritual wellness.
actors: Quincy Jones, Common, Russell Simmons, Fat Joe

title: Fight for Justice: David & Me
description: After a convicted killer helps him turn his life around, a young filmmaker sets out to prove that his incarcerated friend is innocent of the crime.

title: FIGHTWORLD
description: Actor and fight enthusiast Frank Grillo travels the world, immersing himself in different fight cultures to understand their traditions and motivations.

title: Figures of Speech
description: In this documentary, passionate high schoolers travel the country and come of age during a turbulent yearlong prep for a national speech competition.

title: Filmworker
description: Leon Vitali had a thriving acting career most others would envy. Then he gave it all up to devote himself completely to the vision of Stanley Kubrick.

title: Finders Keepers
description: When Shannon Whisnant finds an amputated leg in a used grill, he tries to capitalize on the mass-media frenzy. But then the limb's owner shows up.

title: Finding Vivian Maier
description: By all accounts, Vivian Maier was an unassuming nanny. But the photos she took that were found only after her death reveal her artistic genius.

title: First and Last
description: Take an intimate look at the emotionally charged first and last days of new and soon-to-be released inmates at Georgia's Gwinnett County Jail.

title: Fishtail
description: Harry Dean Stanton narrates this documentary that follows two modern-day cowboys as they welcome new calves at Montana's Fishtail Basin Ranch.

title: Five Came Back
description: Five acclaimed contemporary directors tell the story of five legendary Hollywood filmmakers who enlisted in the armed forces to document World War II.
actors: Steven Spielberg, Guillermo del Toro, Lawrence Kasdan, Francis Ford Coppola

title: Floyd Norman: An Animated Life
description: Charming original animated sequences blend with interviews and archive footage to chronicle the unique career of Disney animator Floyd Norman.

title: Follow This
description: Follow the reporters at BuzzFeed as they probe topics ranging from quirky internet crazes to safe injection spaces for opioid users.
actors: John Stanton, Scaachi Koul, Azeen Ghorayshi, Bim Adewunmi

title: Foo Fighters: Back and Forth
description: The history of the Foo Fighters comes alive in this documentary, from their demo tapes through the creation of their 2011 album "Wasting Light."

title: Food, Inc.
description: Director Robert Kenner's provocative, Oscar-nominated documentary looks at the food industry's harmful effects on human health and the environment.

title: For Grace
description: As chef Curtis Duffy oversees every aspect of opening his own restaurant, Grace, he recalls his turbulent childhood and difficult adult relationships.

title: For the Love of Spock
description: The son of actor Leonard Nimoy directs this moving look at his father's portrayal of Spock, the iconic "Star Trek" character he played for 50 years.
actors: Leonard Nimoy, William Shatner, George Takei, Nichelle Nichols

title: Forks Over Knives
description: According to the research of two food scientists, the popularity of processed foods has led to epidemic rates of obesity, diabetes and other diseases.

title: Frank and Cindy
description: Frank was a rising pop star when he married Cindy, but decades of dashed dreams and alcoholism have left the pair struggling to find happiness.

title: Freeway: Crack in the System
description: Take in the true account of drug kingpin "Freeway" Rick Ross's empire and how the CIA helped him fuel America's  devastating crack cocaine epidemic.

title: Fresh Dressed
description: Though it sprang from the depths of black culture, hip-hop fashion has spread to the masses and taken on a whole new meaning.

title: From One Second to the Next
description: Werner Herzog chronicles the devastating consequences of texting and driving. The film examines how lives can be forever altered by a trivial text.

title: Frontline Fighting: Battling ISIS
description: Cameras follow three Brits -- a former IT worker, an ex-currency trader and a soldier turned activist -- who've signed up to fight ISIS in Syria.

title: Full Force Nature
description: Witness the amazing destructive power of nature as cameras capture harrowing footage of flash floods, tsunamis, mudslides, ice storms and hurricanes.

title: Functional Fitness
description: This documentary explores the challenging, transformative world of high-intensity fitness programs through the eyes of the people who've embraced them.
